{"type":"message","id":"b16f9d10","parentId":"80f7c6d7","timestamp":"2026-03-15T07:47:57.582Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the issue - the process tool requires a sessionId for exec actions, but I don't have a way to create a session without already having one. Let me check the process tool description again... It says \"Manage running exec sessions: list, poll, log, write, send-keys, submit, paste, kill.\" \n\nLooking at the action parameter, it seems like \"exec\" might not be the right action. Let me look at what actions are available. The description mentions actions like list, poll, log, write, send-keys, submit, paste, kill. There's no \"exec\" action mentioned.\n\nLet me try a different approach - I'll try to read files directly by guessing common documentation file names, or I can use the web_fetch tool if there are URLs, but that's not applicable here.\n\nActually, let me try reading some common documentation files that might exist in the docs directory.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_7f5951f61f06499fb59dd593","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"F:\\Program\\nvm\\node_global\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\API.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"dashscope-coding","model":"qwen3.5-plus","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773560873632}}
